  {panel}

JIRA Service Desk automation is no longer working after latest release.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2248].
  {panel}

It would be nice to have an option on the Service Desk settings where the customers could create issues by email and/or reply the notifications setting other users in the CC field that are not in the system to automatically be a new Service Desk customer and be a participant of the specific issue mentioned on the email (e.g Option as _Customers can add new customers to their requests_).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2247].
  {panel}

As a Service Desk Portal User, I will be able to see the progress of a ticket. However, if an Agent modifies any comment, I won't have any visibility to the changes or update on that comment.

From the Agent point of view however, they will be able to know that the comment has been *edited*, by whom and the original comment before edited. There is also an indicator to show that the comment has been edited.

It will be great, if Service Desk Portal User also able to see that a comment has been edited, and by whom.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2246].
  {panel}

h5. Issue summary
Currently, JIRA Service Desk notification says the following:
{quote}If the Notifications setting for JIRA Service Desk is disabled, the JIRA notification scheme works as defined for all users, including customers{quote}
- Though this is true, from prior tests, if the customer is not a JIRA user(belongs to one of the 3 JIRA groups that count towards your license), they would receive no notification.

Can this be added into the documentation and if it happens that it is a bug and JSD customer who are not JIRA users should be able to receive notifications can this be fixed?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2240].
  {panel}

As a Service Desk Administrator, I would like to add a form as an attachment, where I would need my customer to fill in, and attach it back into the ticket.

Having a read-only Custom Field URL field or this functionality itself into the Request Form will help me to achieve this use case.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2235].
  {panel}

h3. Summary
When entering data into a single line text field in a Service Desk request, and this data exceeds the limit, you receive a message {{There was an error initialising the workflow}}

h3. Environment
* JIRA 7.0.0
* Service Desk 2.6.0

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a custom text field (single line)
# Add this field on the Create Issue screen for a JIRA Project that is associated with a Service Desk.
# Update the Service Desk customer portal to request this field.
# Create a request on that Service Desk, while pasting the following paragraph into the custom field:
{quote}Integer sagittis nisi vel rhoncus molestie. Aenean vehicula, ipsum id hendrerit sollicitudin, leo risus porttitor odio, eget ullamcorper dui tellus et magna. Mauris vitae justo ac neque pellentesque ultricies non sed libero. Maecenas sit amet neque ac arcu tristique elementum. Integer diam sapien, vestibulum eget accumsan nec, ultricies sit amet nisl. Vivamus et nisi nec risus laoreet suscipit at et erat. Ut a nisl a nibh imperdiet molestie vulputate id libero. Ut tincidunt sagittis ultricies. Praesent sit amet magna sagittis, volutpat magna ut, convallis orci. Mauris quam quam, gravida id quam non, accumsan finibus risus. Aenean diam neque, varius a neque non, auctor congue dui. Maecenas placerat lectus velit, in tincidunt nunc rutrum eu. Curabitur mollis ipsum ac nisi convallis vestibulum. Maecenas porta ex non enim dignissim, eget ultricies arcu finibus. Etiam commodo, turpis nec scelerisque volutpat, dolor magna aliquam nisl, non elementum mauris purus sit amet urna. Vivamus vel odio sed mauris vestibulum tincidunt rhoncus ut tortuur.{quote}
# Submit.

