h3. Workaround
Reduce the length of the data in the custom text fields.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2233].
  {panel}

Currently in JIRA Service Desk, if a field is specified as required, in the {{Service Desk > Your Project > Request Type > Edit field}} page, there is no marking or indication that the field is required when customers are creating an issue for that request type from the customer's portal.

The only way they get to know that it is required is after it fails should they leave it empty.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2228].
  {panel}

