  {panel}

h5. Summary:
A customer would like to be able to see all issues that make up a particular node in the JIRA Service Desk report page.

{quote}
When we click on a node in a report graph of a service desk project, we would like to see all the tickets mentioned in that node. For example: Report about Time to Resolution Met and Breached. When we click on the node of the yesterday breached tickets, we would like to see a filter containing all these tickets.
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2217].
  {panel}

When you have at least one required field on the edit screen, you can not edit Request Type in Inline Edit mode. 

Executing this: http://localhost:8080/rest/servicedesk/1/servicedesk/request/10111/request-types
returns a message: 


{code:java}
{"errors":[{"errorMessage":"Failed to validate update parameters of the given request"}],"reasonKey"
:"com.atlassian.servicedesk.internal.feature.customer.request.RequestUpdateValidationError","reasonCode"
:"400"}
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2211].
  {panel}

When you mention a collaborator on an Service Desk ticket, JIRA sends a different notification, where the {{reply-to}} header is not the account configured in JIRA Service Desk mail handler.

This can lead to confusion, as when one agent mentions a collaborator on an ticket, like to get approval or guidance on some procedure, and the reply by mail from the collaborator should update the Service Desk ticket, but currently the message just gets lost.

This behavior is already implemented in JIRA itself ([JRA-30852|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-30852]) and Service Desk should comply with it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2209].
  {panel}

h5. Issue Summary
Customer would like to be able to customize the URL of their Service Desk so it matches with each of their customer's portals as described below:
{quote}
We have a new service desk portal.
At the moment our URL is jira.emakina.nl

For this customer, we want to create a URL like:

servicedesk.<customer>.emakina.nl which will direct to the servicedesk.

It would be great if the URL doesn't change.
{quote}

Our current Set up is Service Desk follow: {{baseURL+ServiceDesk added paths to portal}}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2208].
  {panel}

h5. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a new Service Desk.
# Configure a request type to allow attachment.
# Create an issue from customer portal and attach an image.
# Use the wiki renderer to notation for attaching an image to add the image {code}!myImage.jpg!{code}

*Expected Result*
Service Desk would show the attached image and render the image in the description once done.

*Actual Result*
Image is attached and can be seen in attachment however the image is not rendered in both JIRA and customer portal showing up simply as  {code}!myImage.jpg!{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2200].
  {panel}

In our use case the worklogs are used as input for our billing on projects, therefore we would like to make Service Desk Collaborators to be able to log their work on the requests which they help to resolve.

E.g. a project team needs an IT engineer's help in resolving a bug in a project environment, he works on the fix for 1 hours. We would like to have this 1 hour to be logged on the project he worked on, however we do not want to include him as a project team member as he has no active role on the project and we do not want him to view the queues, reports, SLA metrics, or participate in the customer-facing as Agents do so.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2197].
  {panel}

h5. Issue Summary
Customer would like to be able to specify the way fields are arranged in Service Desk customer portal.

If fields are arranged in a particular order in the Request type page, that order should be maintained when the user views the issue in customer portal rather than reverting to the default format used within JIRA.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2195].
  {panel}

We would involv the Customer into the workflow to set activ a status (e.g. to order, to accept something)
also it would be nice if a customer has to fill a custom field based on a status.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2191].
  {panel}

The holidays added to a ServiceDesk calendar are sorted by creation and not by date of the actual holiday.
For a better overview the holidays should be sorted and displayed by date.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2190].
  {panel}

The Service Desk queues are based on the results of a filter query.
The orientation or sorting of displayed issues in the queues can only be adjusted by admins, and any changes applied carry over for all users. The orientation is put into the JQL that populates the queues with issues.
As an Agent, I would like to be able to change the orientation or sorting of issues that are displayed, without this impacting other Agents working on the same queues (Like the JIRA Issue Navigator).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2189].
  {panel}

The Service Desk queues are based on the results of a filter query.
The columns displayed in the queues can only be adjusted by admins, and any changes applied carry over for all users.
As an Agent, I would like to be able to customize the columns that are displayed, without this impacting other Agents working on the same queues (Like the JIRA Issue Navigator).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2188].
  {panel}

It would be beneficial to have the option to add to SLA reports the ability to use JQL and select a drop down on the report that goes back further than a year.

!|DropDown.pngthumbnail!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2183].
  {panel}


We currently have a request from a customer to get Announcer for JIRA announcements to show up on the portals however JSD doesn't support web panels :(

It would be great to be able to use web-panel functionality within the customer portal.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2178].
  {panel}

Customer would like to customize the title added to notifications that are sent to issue reporters.

They would like it to be only the issue id or (ticket number).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2176].
  {panel}

When changing the logo from Help Center, for some logos after saving changes it come back for the previously one.
This is not happening for all images and I could find the reason why some of them worked and other don't. Exemple of image that is not working is attached.

It seems to be an issue with monochromatic images. If the image has at least one non-white pixel the upload will work.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2175].
  {panel}

Customer requested that when creating an issue within Service Desk customer portal, he would like to have a specific Field A shown, however when creating an issue within the same project, he would like the field to be hidden.

{quote}
Our service desk request type A is mapped to our issue type B. Due to its screen scheme, issue type B has a "Default" screen and a screen for the "Create Issue" operation.
Field C is availble in the "Default" screen but is not removed from the "Create Issue" screen. Field "C" might, for example, be the field "Fix Version/s", which is not necessary when creating a new issue.
However, I want field C to be visible for the customers inside the Sevice Desk customer portal. Therefore I want to add field C inside the Service Desk settings (Service Desk > Request type > Request type A > Edit fields > Add a field). But field C does not appear inside the selection. Apparently, only the fields configured for the "Create issue" screen appear here, even though the field selection for the request type is used for all operations inside the customer portal.
Is this working as intended or a bug? If it is w.a.i., what is a possible workaround to not see field C when creating issue type B inside JIRA but to see field C inside the customer portal?
{quote}

He would like  the customer portal not to follow the JIRA specified screen scheme.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2171].
  {panel}

The customer portal is designed to ensure that only the reporter and participants of an issue can see it, as well as agents.

But if anonymous access is enabled, currently everyone becomes able to see every issue, including internal and external comments.

Therefore, the solution seems to be that it should not be possible for an anonymous user to have access to a Service Desk project.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2168].
  {panel}

